{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883817612,"sessionID":"ses_2851506ccffefkIVb2j6EWAN4H","part":{"id":"prt_d7aebcca30010cbZ6f6l6WHBLR","messageID":"msg_d7aebbfa7001ixN4a7g8CQswFP","sessionID":"ses_2851506ccffefkIVb2j6EWAN4H","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b2e65ab3ad254b06881aa4f8","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\n**AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试**\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. The SDK follows a layered architecture:\n\n- **Public API Layer** (`agentcube/__init__.py`): Exposes `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **High-Level Clients** (`code_interpreter.py`, `agent_runtime.py`): User-facing clients with business logic\n- **Low-Level Clients** (`clients/`): HTTP communication with control plane and data plane\n- **Utilities** (`utils/`): HTTP session management, logging, file I/O helpers\n\n## 2. Package Layout\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py                    # Public exports (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n├── code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient\n├── agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntimeClient\n├── exceptions.py                  # Exception hierarchy\n├── clients/\n│   ├── __init__.py                # Re-exports data plane clients\n│   ├── control_plane.py          # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager)\n│   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n└── utils/\n    ├── __init__.py\n    ├── http.py                    # create_session\n    ├── utils.py                   # read_token_from_file\n    └── log.py                     # get_logger\n\ntests/\n├── test_code_interpreter.py       # Tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n├── test_agent_runtime_client.py   # Tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n├── test_control_plane.py          # Tests for ControlPlaneClient\n├── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n├── test_http.py\n├── test_utils.py\n└── test_exceptions.py\n```\n\n## 3. Public API Surface\n\n### 3.1 Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n### 3.2 Client Exports (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n\n```python\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n## 4. Client Classes\n\n### 4.1 CodeInterpreterClient (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n\n**Purpose**: High-level client for Code Interpreter sessions.\n\n**Constructor Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Session name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n| `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token for control plane |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n\n**Instance Attributes**:\n- `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`: Configuration values\n- `logger`: Logger instance\n- `cp_client`: ControlPlaneClient instance\n- `router_url`: Router URL string\n- `session_id`: Current session ID\n- `dp_client`: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient instance\n\n**Methods**:\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n| `stop()` | Cleanup session and close clients |\n| `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n| `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code in specified language |\n| `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file to remote session |\n| `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload local file |\n| `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download remote file |\n| `list_files(path)` | List files in remote path |\n\n### 4.2 AgentRuntimeClient (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n\n**Purpose**: High-level client for Agent Runtime invocations.\n\n**Constructor Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | `\"my-agent\"` | Agent name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n\n**Instance Attributes**:\n- `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`: Configuration\n- `logger`: Logger instance\n- `router_url`: Router URL string\n- `session_id`: Current session ID\n- `dp_client`: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance\n\n**Methods**:\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n| `invoke(payload, timeout)` | Invoke agent with payload |\n| `close()` | Close client and release resources |\n\n### 4.3 ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n\n**Purpose**: Low-level client for Workload Manager (control plane) operations.\n\n**Constructor Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL (required) |\n| `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n| `pool_connections` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool connections |\n| `pool_maxsize` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool max size |\n\n**Methods**:\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `create_session(name, namespace, metadata, ttl)` | Create new session, returns sessionId |\n| `delete_session(session_id)` | Delete session (404 returns True) |\n| `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### 4.4 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n\n**Purpose**: Low-level client for Code Interpreter data plane operations.\n\n**Constructor Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `session_id` | `str` | Required | Session identifier |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n| `namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Namespace |\n| `cr_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom resource name |\n| `base_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Explicit base URL |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n\n**Methods**:\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n| `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code |\n| `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file (base64) |\n| `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload file (multipart) |\n| `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download file (stream) |\n| `list_files(path)` | List files |\n| `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n\n### 4.5 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n**Purpose**: Low-level client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n\n**Class Constant**:\n- `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n**Constructor Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `router_url` | `str` | Required | Router URL |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Required | Namespace |\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Agent name |\n| `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n\n**Methods**:\n| Method | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `bootstrap_session_id()` | GET to fetch session ID from header |\n| `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` | POST JSON payload |\n| `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n\n## 5. HTTP API Contracts\n\n### 5.1 Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n\n| Method | Path | Body | Response |\n|--------|------|------|----------|\n| `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"sessionId\": \"...\"}` |\n| `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 200 or 404 (treated as success) |\n\n**Headers**:\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token provided)\n\n### 5.2 Data Plane — Code Interpreter\n\n**Base URL Construction**:\n```\n{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\n```\n\n| Method | Relative Path | Body | Notes |\n|--------|---------------|------|-------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = timeout + 2s |\n| `POST` | `api/files` (JSON) | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | |\n| `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | Stream for download |\n| `GET` | `api/files?path=...` | — | List files |\n\n**Headers**:\n- Default: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON: `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n### 5.3 Data Plane — Agent Runtime\n\n**Base URL Construction**:\n```\n{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n```\n\n| Method | Path | Headers | Body |\n|--------|------|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | JSON payload |\n\n## 6. Configuration Resolution\n\nThere is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed:\n\n| Component | Resolved from |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient base_url | `workload_manager_url` arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| ControlPlaneClient auth | `auth_token` arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n| CodeInterpreterClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| AgentRuntimeClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| Default timeouts | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` for all clients |\n| Pool settings | `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n\n## 7. Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    exit_code: int\n    stderr: str\n    command: Optional[str]\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation/management fails\"\"\"\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n```\n\n## 8. Utility Functions\n\n### 8.1 `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n\nCreates `requests.Session` with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n\n### 8.2 `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n\nReads file contents as token string. Returns `None` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n\n### 8.3 `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n\nReturns `logging.Logger` with configurable level (INFO default, DEBUG if verbose).\n\n## 9. Testing Strategy\n\n### 9.1 Test Framework\n\n- **pytest** with **pytest-mock** for mocking\n- **pytest-asyncio** for async tests\n- **pytest-cov** for coverage\n\n### 9.2 Test Organization\n\nTests mirror the source structure:\n- `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` — High-level client tests\n- `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` — High-level client tests\n- `tests/test_control_plane.py` — Control plane HTTP tests\n- `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n- `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n- `tests/test_http.py` — HTTP utility tests\n- `tests/test_utils.py` — Utility function tests\n- `tests/test_exceptions.py` — Exception hierarchy tests\n\n### 9.3 Test Patterns\n\n**Unit Tests**: Mock HTTP responses to test client logic without network calls.\n\n**Integration Points**:\n- Environment variable resolution (ROUTER_URL, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL)\n- Token file reading from Kubernetes service account path\n- Context manager lifecycle (enter/exit)\n- Session bootstrap via GET request\n\n**Error Scenarios**:\n- Non-zero exit codes → CommandExecutionError\n- Missing session headers → ValueError\n- Network failures → SessionError/DataPlaneError\n- 404 on delete → Returns True (success)\n\n### 9.4 Coverage Areas\n\n| Component | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| CodeInterpreterClient | Constructor, context manager, execute_command, run_code, file operations, stop |\n| AgentRuntimeClient | Constructor, bootstrap, invoke, close |\n| ControlPlaneClient | Create session, delete session (404 handling), auth headers |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | URL construction, execute, run_code, files API, download, list |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | Bootstrap, invoke, timeout handling |\n| Utils | HTTP session, logger, token reading |\n| Exceptions | All exception classes and attributes |\n\n## 10. Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n```\n\nBuild requirements:\n- `setuptools>=61.0`\n- `wheel`\n- Python >=3.10\n\n## 11. Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n| Requirement | Verified By |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup`, `test_stop_closes_clients` |\n| AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_bootstrap_session`, `test_close` |\n| HTTP client contracts | `test_create_session_success`, `test_delete_session_not_found`, `test_execute_command`, `test_invoke` |\n| Session header management | `test_constructor_session_header`, `test_session_header_constant` |\n| Exception hierarchy | `test_command_execution_error_attributes`, `test_session_error_inherits`, `test_data_plane_error_inherits` |\n| Timeout behavior | `test_execute_command_with_timeout`, `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775883817605,"end":1775883817610}}}}
