{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883824442,"sessionID":"ses_2851506ccffefkIVb2j6EWAN4H","part":{"id":"prt_d7aeca962001hsdZFVOxoVRGi6","messageID":"msg_d7aec9fd6001zSlax29VhHTQj5","sessionID":"ses_2851506ccffefkIVb2j6EWAN4H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_16564686b07c4ace8c787794","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-021\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n5: - **Language**: Python\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: cmd/cli/\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\n20: ├── agentcube/\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports app, runtimes\n22: │   ├── cli/\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\n25: │   ├── models/\n26: │   │   └── pack_models.py                      # MetadataOptions dataclass\n27: │   ├── runtime/\n28: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n29: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                     # PackRuntime\n30: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py                    # BuildRuntime\n31: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py                  # PublishRuntime\n32: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py                   # InvokeRuntime\n33: │   │   └── status_runtime.py                   # StatusRuntime\n34: │   ├── services/\n35: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # Services package docstring\n36: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py                 # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n37: │   │   ├── docker_service.py                   # DockerService\n38: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py                     # KubernetesProvider\n39: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py               # AgentCubeProvider\n40: │   └── operations/\n41: │       └── __init__.py                         # Placeholder module docstring\n42: └── examples/\n43:     ├── hello-agent/\n44:     │   └── main.py                             # Example agent\n45:     └── math-agent/\n46:         └── main.py                             # Example agent\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### 1.3 Console Script Entry Point\n50: \n51: ```toml\n52: [project.scripts]\n53: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n54: ```\n55: \n56: The CLI is invoked as `kubectl-agentcube` with subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`.\n57: \n58: ## 2. Command Specifications\n59: \n60: ### 2.1 Global Options\n61: \n62: The root callback accepts:\n63: \n64: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n65: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n66: | `--version` | Optional[bool] | None | Show version and exit (eager option) |\n67: | `--verbose`, `-v` | bool | False | Enable verbose output |\n68: \n69: **Version Output**: `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` using Rich markup.\n70: \n71: **Verbose Behavior**: When `--verbose` is passed, `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` is called.\n72: \n73: ### 2.2 pack Command\n74: \n75: Validates and prepares a workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile.\n76: \n77: ```python\n78: def pack(\n79:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n80:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n81:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n82:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n83:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n84:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n85:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n86:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n87:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n88: ) -> None:\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Success Output**: Prints success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` using Rich `Progress` spinner.\n92: \n93: ### 2.3 build Command\n94: \n95: Builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local`.\n96: \n97: ```python\n98: def build(\n99:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n100:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n101:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n102:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n103:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n104: ) -> None:\n105: ```\n106: \n107: **Version Increment**: Increments `metadata.version` (patch bump for X.Y.Z, or append .1 / fallback {version}-1) before build and reverts on failure.\n108: \n109: ### 2.4 publish Command\n110: \n111: Publishes/deploys using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service).\n112: \n113: ```python\n114: def publish(\n115:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n116:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n117:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL\"),\n118:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n119:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n120:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n121:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n122:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name\"),\n123:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n124:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"NodePort (30000-32767)\"),\n125:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas\"),\n126:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"Deployment namespace\"),\n127:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n128: ) -> None:\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### 2.5 invoke Command\n132: \n133: POSTs JSON to the published agent endpoint.\n134: \n135: ```python\n136: def invoke(\n137:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n138:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n139:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers\"),\n140:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n141:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n142: ) -> None:\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Header Format**: Headers are parsed as `key:value` format. Invalid format prints error and exits with code 1.\n146: \n147: **Session Header**: If metadata contains `session_id`, adds header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` to request.\n148: \n149: ### 2.6 status Command\n150: \n151: Loads workspace metadata and displays agent status in a Rich `Table`.\n152: \n153: ```python\n154: def status(\n155:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n156:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\"),\n157:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n158: ) -> None:\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Exit Codes**: Exits with code 1 when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n162: \n163: ## 3. Runtime Classes\n164: \n165: ### 3.1 PackRuntime\n166: \n167: Handles workspace validation, metadata loading/creation, Dockerfile generation.\n168: \n169: ```python\n170: class PackRuntime:\n171:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n172:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n173:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n174:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n175:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n176:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n177:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n178:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n179:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n180:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ### 3.2 BuildRuntime\n184: \n185: Manages Docker image build process with local and cloud modes.\n186: \n187: ```python\n188: class BuildRuntime:\n189:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n190:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n191:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n192:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n193:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n194:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### 3.3 PublishRuntime\n198: \n199: Handles deployment to AgentCube or Kubernetes.\n200: \n201: ```python\n202: class PublishRuntime:\n203:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n204:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n206:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n207:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### 3.4 InvokeRuntime\n211: \n212: Handles agent invocation via HTTP.\n213: \n214: ```python\n215: class InvokeRuntime:\n216:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n217:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n218:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n219:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n220: ```\n221: \n222: **Known Issue**: `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` may raise `UnboundLocalError` if `endpoint` doesn't start with `http`.\n223: \n224: ### 3.5 StatusRuntime\n225: \n226: Retrieves and displays agent status.\n227: \n228: ```python\n229: class StatusRuntime:\n230:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n231:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n232:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n233:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## 4. Services\n237: \n238: ### 4.1 DockerService\n239: \n240: ```python\n241: class DockerService:\n242:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n243:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n244:     def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n245:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n246:     def push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n247:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 4.2 MetadataService\n251: \n252: ```python\n253: class MetadataService:\n254:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n255:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n256:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n257:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n258:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n259: ```\n260: \n261: **Metadata File**: Saved to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`.\n262: \n263: ### 4.3 KubernetesProvider\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: class KubernetesProvider:\n267:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n268:     def deploy_agent(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, replicas: int = 1, node_port: Optional[int] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n269:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n270:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n271:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### 4.4 AgentCubeProvider\n275: \n276: ```python\n277: class AgentCubeProvider:\n278:     def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n279:     def deploy_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n280:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n281: ```\n282: \n283: **CR API**: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n284: \n285: ## 5. Data Models\n286: \n287: ### 5.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n288: \n289: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n290: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n291: | `agent_name` | str | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n292: | `description` | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n293: | `language` | str | \"python\" | Programming language used |\n294: | `entrypoint` | str | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n295: | `port` | int | 8080 | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n296: | `build_mode` | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n297: | `region` | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n298: | `version` | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string for publishing |\n299: | `image` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Container image information |\n300: | `auth` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Authentication configuration |\n301: | `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n302: | `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry URL for image publishing |\n303: | `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry username |\n304: | `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry password |\n305: | `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | None | Agent endpoint URL |\n306: | `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for the Workload Manager |\n307: | `router_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for the Router |\n308: | `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | None | Path for the readiness probe |\n309: | `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | None | Port for the readiness probe |\n310: | `agent_id` | Optional[str] | None | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n311: | `session_id` | Optional[str] | None | The session ID for the agent |\n312: | `k8s_deployment` | Optional[Dict[str, Any]] | None | Kubernetes deployment information |\n313: \n314: **Validators**:\n315: - `validate_language`: ['python', 'java'] lowercase\n316: - `validate_build_mode`: ['local', 'cloud'] lowercase\n317: - `validate_port`: 1..65535\n318: \n319: ### 5.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n320: \n321: | Field | Type | Default |\n322: |-------|------|---------|\n323: | `agent_name` | Optional[str] | None |\n324: | `language` | Optional[str] | 'python' |\n325: | `entrypoint` | Optional[str] | None |\n326: | `port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n327: | `build_mode` | Optional[str] | 'local' |\n328: | `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | None |\n329: | `description` | Optional[str] | None |\n330: | `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n331: | `router_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n332: | `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n333: | `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n334: | `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n335: | `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n336: | `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n337: | `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n338: \n339: ## 6. Dependencies\n340: \n341: ### 6.1 Required Dependencies\n342: \n343: ```toml\n344: dependencies = [\n345:     \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n346:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n347:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n348:     \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n349:     \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n350:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n351:     \"packaging>=23.0\",\n352:     \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n353:     \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n354: ]\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ### 6.2 Optional Dependencies\n358: \n359: ```toml\n360: [project.optional-dependencies]\n361: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n362: dev = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"ruff>=0.1.0\", \"mypy>=1.5.0\", \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\", \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n363: test = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\", \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\"]\n364: ```\n365: \n366: **Python Version**: `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n367: \n368: ## 7. Error Handling\n369: \n370: ### 7.1 Error Handler Function\n371: \n372: ```python\n373: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n374:     # prints \"Error {command_name}: {e}\" in red\n375:     # if verbose, prints full traceback\n376:     # raises typer.Exit(1)\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### 7.2 Common Errors\n380: \n381: | Error | Scenario | Exit Code |\n382: |-------|----------|-----------|\n383: | Workspace not found | Invalid workspace path | 1 |\n384: | Docker unavailable | build command with local mode | 1 |\n385: | Invalid payload | invoke with malformed JSON | 1 |\n386: | Invalid header format | invoke with malformed header | 1 |\n387: | Not published | status command with no agent_id | 1 |\n388: \n389: ## 8. Testing Strategy\n390: \n391: ### 8.1 Unit Tests\n392: \n393: Test each runtime class and service with mocked dependencies.\n394: \n395: ### 8.2 Integration Tests\n396: \n397: - End-to-end CLI command tests\n398: - Docker integration tests (requires Docker)\n399: - K8s integration tests (requires test cluster)\n400: \n401: ### 8.3 Build Verification\n402: \n403: ```bash\n404: # Install CLI\n405: pip install -e cmd/cli/\n406: \n407: # Verify entry point\n408: kubectl-agentcube --help\n409: \n410: # Run tests\n411: pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: # AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n417: \n418: - **AR ID**: AR-019\n419: - **Module**: cmd\n420: - **Language**: Go\n421: - **Size**: M\n422: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n423: \n424: ## 1. Architecture\n425: \n426: ### 1.1 Overview\n427: \n428: AgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n429: \n430: ### 1.2 Binary Overview\n431: \n432: | Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n433: |--------|---------|------|--------------|\n434: | `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n435: | `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |\n436: | `router` | HTTP Session Router | 8080 | Redis/Valkey, WorkloadManager |\n437: | `workload-manager` | Sandbox Lifecycle Manager | 8080 | K8s API Server, Redis/Valkey |\n438: \n439: ### 1.3 Component Structure\n440: \n441: ```\n442: cmd/\n443: ├── agentd/\n444: │   ├── main.go                      # Controller entry point\n445: │   └── ...\n446: ├── picod/\n447: │   ├── main.go                      # Code execution daemon entry\n448: │   └── ...\n449: ├── router/\n450: │   ├── main.go                      # Router entry point\n451: │   └── ...\n452: └── workload-manager/\n453:     ├── main.go                      # Workload manager entry point\n454:     └── ...\n455: ```\n456: \n457: ### 1.4 Architecture Diagram\n458: \n459: ```\n460: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n461: │                              AgentCube System                                │\n462: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n463: │                                                                             │\n464: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n465: │  │                        agentd (Controller)                           │   │\n466: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n467: │  │  │  Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CRDs                 │  │   │\n468: │  │  │  Creates: Pods, Services, ConfigMaps                          │  │   │\n469: │  │  │  Status Updates: AgentRuntimeStatus, CodeInterpreterStatus    │  │   │\n470: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n471: │  └──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n472: │                                 │                                             │\n473: │                                 │ K8s API                                     │\n474: │                                 ▼                                             │\n475: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n476: │  │                    Kubernetes API Server                             │   │\n477: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │   │\n478: │  │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pod/Service/Config │   │   │\n479: │  │  │ (CRD)          │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Native resources)│   │   │\n480: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │   │\n481: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n482: │                                    │                                         │\n483: ├────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\n484: │                                    │                                         │\n485: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n486: │  │                    workload-manager                                 │   │\n487: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n488: │  │  │ HTTP API    │  │ Sandbox CRUD │  │ Session Lifecycle       │   │   │\n489: │  │  │ (Gin)       │  │              │  │                         │   │   │\n490: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n491: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n492: │                                 │                                           │\n493: │                                 │ Session events                            │\n494: │                                 ▼                                           │\n495: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n496: │  │                    Redis/Valkey (Session Store)                     │   │\n497: │  │  - Session data (session-routing)                                   │   │\n498: │  │  - Sandbox state                                                    │   │\n499: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n500: │                                    │                                         │\n501: │                                    │ Proxy routing                           │\n502: │                                    ▼                                         │\n503: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n504: │  │                         router                                      │   │\n505: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n506: │  │  │ Session     │  │ Auth/JWT    │  │ Backend Health Check    │   │   │\n507: │  │  │ Routing     │  │ Middleware  │  │                          │   │   │\n508: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n509: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n510: │                                 │                                           │\n511: │                                 │ HTTP Requests                             │\n512: │                                 ▼                                           │\n513: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n514: │  │                      Sandbox Pods                                   │   │\n515: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n516: │  │  │ Agent        │  │ Code         │  │ Services                 │   │   │\n517: │  │  │ Container    │  │ Interpreter  │  │ (NodePort/ClusterIP)    │   │   │\n518: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n519: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n520: │                                    │                                         │\n521: │                                    │ Optional                                │\n522: │                                    ▼                                         │\n523: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n524: │  │                         picod                                       │   │\n525: │  │  - Code execution daemon inside sandbox pods                       │   │\n526: │  │  - File operations, execution                                       │   │\n527: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n528: │                                                                             │\n529: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n530: ```\n531: \n532: ### 1.5 Data Flow\n533: \n534: ```\n535:                                     ┌─────────────────┐\n536:                                     │   Client Request│\n537:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n538:                                              │\n539:                                              ▼\n540:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n541:                                │      router             │\n542:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n543:                                │  │ Auth Middleware   │  │\n544:                                │  │ JWT/Token Review  │  │\n545:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n546:                                │            │            │\n547:                                │            ▼            │\n548:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n549:                                │  │ Session Manager   │  │\n550:                                │  │ → Redis lookup    │  │\n551:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n552:                                │            │            │\n553:                                │            ▼            │\n554:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n555:                                │  │ Backend Selector  │  │\n556:                                │  │ → WorkloadManager │  │\n557:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n558:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n559:                                            │\n560:                                            ▼\n561:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n562:                                │  workload-manager      │\n563:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n564:                                │  │ API Handlers      │  │\n565:                                │  │ GET/POST/DELETE   │  │\n566:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n567:                                │            │            │\n568:                                │            ▼            │\n569:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n570:                                │  │ Client-go         │  │\n571:                                │  │ → K8s API         │  │\n572:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n573:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n574:                                            │\n575:                                            ▼\n576:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n577:                                │  Kubernetes API Server  │\n578:                                │  - Create AgentRuntime │\n579:                                │  - Create Pod/Service  │\n580:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n581:                                            │\n582:                                            ▼\n583:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n584:                                │      agentd             │\n585:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n586:                                │  │ Controller        │  │\n587:                                │  │ → Reconcile loop  │  │\n588:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n589:                                └─────────────────────────┘\n590: ```\n591: \n592: ## 2. Binary Specifications\n593: \n594: ### 2.1 agentd — Kubernetes Controller\n595: \n596: **Entry Point**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n597: \n598: The agentd binary runs as a Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime. It watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state.\n599: \n600: #### Command-Line Flags\n601: \n602: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n603: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n604: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Metrics server bind address (0 = disabled) |\n605: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Health probe bind address |\n606: | `--leader-elect` | bool | false | Enable leader election |\n607: | `--leader-elect-lease-duration` | duration | 15s | Leader election lease duration |\n608: | `--leader-elect-renew-deadline` | duration | 10s | Leader election renew deadline |\n609: | `--leader-elect-retry-period` | duration | 5s | Leader election retry period |\n610: \n611: #### Configuration\n612: \n613: ```go\n614: type AgentdConfig struct {\n615:     // Metrics server configuration\n616:     MetricsBindAddress string\n617:     \n618:     // Health probe configuration  \n619:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n620:     \n621:     // Leader election\n622:     LeaderElect        bool\n623:     LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n624:     RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n625:     RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n626:     \n627:     // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n628:     WatchNamespace     string\n629:     \n630:     // Sync period for full reconciliation\n631:     SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n632:     \n633:     // Max concurrent reconciles\n634:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n635: }\n636: ```\n637: \n638: #### Dependencies\n639: \n640: - `pkg/agentd/` — Controller implementation\n641: - `pkg/client/informers/` — Generated informers\n642: - `pkg/client/listers/` — Generated listers\n643: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — API types\n644: \n645: ### 2.2 picod — Code Execution Daemon\n646: \n647: **Entry Point**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n648: \n649: The picod binary runs inside sandbox pods as a code execution daemon, providing file operations and code execution capabilities.\n650: \n651: #### Command-Line Flags\n652: \n653: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n654: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n655: | `--port` | int | 8080 | Server listen port |\n656: | `--workspace` | string | \"\" | Root directory for file operations (default: cwd) |\n657: | `--auth-mode` | string | \"picod\" | Authentication mode: picod, none |\n658: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Session timeout |\n659: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Maximum session duration |\n660: \n661: #### Configuration\n662: \n663: ```go\n664: type PicoDConfig struct {\n665:     Port              int\n666:     Workspace         string\n667:     AuthMode          string\n668:     SessionTimeout    time.Duration\n669:     MaxSessionDuration time.Duration\n670: }\n671: ```\n672: \n673: #### API Endpoints\n674: \n675: | Method | Path | Description |\n676: |--------|------|-------------|\n677: | GET | `/health` | Health check |\n678: | POST | `/execute` | Execute code |\n679: | GET | `/files/*path` | Read file |\n680: | PUT | `/files/*path` | Write file |\n681: | DELETE | `/files/*path` | Delete file |\n682: \n683: #### Dependencies\n684: \n685: - `pkg/picod/` — Server implementation\n686: \n687: ### 2.3 router — HTTP Session Router\n688: \n689: **Entry Point**: `cmd/router/main.go`\n690: \n691: The router binary provides HTTP routing with session management, authentication, and proxy capabilities. It routes incoming requests to the appropriate sandbox backend based on session affinity.\n692: \n693: #### Command-Line Flags\n694: \n695: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n696: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n697: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n698: | `--workload-manager-url` | string | \"\" | WorkloadManager backend URL (required) |\n699: | `--backend-timeout` | duration | 30s | Backend request timeout |\n700: | `--idle-timeout` | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n701: | `--health-check-interval` | duration | 10s | Health check interval |\n702: | `--health-check-timeout` | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n703: | `--max-conns-per-backend` | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n704: | `--rate-limit-enabled` | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n705: | `--rate-limit-rps` | int | 10 | Rate limit RPS |\n706: | `--auth-enabled` | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n707: | `--auth-token` | string | \"\" | Bearer token for auth |\n708: | `--session-enabled` | bool | false | Enable session management |\n709: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 30m | Session timeout |\n710: | `--session-cookie-name` | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Session cookie name |\n711: | `--jwt-enabled` | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n712: | `--jwt-secret` | string | \"\" | JWT secret for HS256 |\n713: | `--jwt-private-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 private key |\n714: | `--jwt-public-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 public key |\n715: \n716: #### Configuration\n717: \n718: ```go\n719: type RouterConfig struct {\n720:     ListenAddress       string\n721:     WorkloadManagerURL string\n722:     \n723:     // Backend\n724:     BackendTimeout      time.Duration\n725:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n726:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n727:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n728:     MaxConnsPerBackend  int\n729:     \n730:     // Rate limiting\n731:     RateLimitEnabled    bool\n732:     RateLimitRPS        int\n733:     \n734:     // Auth\n735:     AuthEnabled         bool\n736:     AuthToken           string\n737:     \n738:     // Session management\n739:     SessionEnabled         bool\n740:     SessionTimeout         time.Duration\n741:     SessionCookieName      string\n742:     SessionMaxActive       int\n743:     SessionCookieSecure    bool\n744:     SessionCookieHTTPOnly  bool\n745:     SessionCookieDomain    string\n746:     SessionCleanupInterval time.Duration\n747:     \n748:     // JWT\n749:     JWTEnabled           bool\n750:     JWTAlgorithm         string\n751:     JWTSecret            string\n752:     JWTPrivateKeyPath    string\n753:     JWTPublicKeyPath     string\n754:     JWTIssuer            string\n755:     JWTAudience          []string\n756:     JWTExpiration        time.Duration\n757:     JWTRefreshExpiration time.Duration\n758:     JWTClockSkew         time.Duration\n759:     JWTAllowQueryParam   bool\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: #### Dependencies\n764: \n765: - `pkg/router/` — Router implementation\n766: - `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n767: - `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n768: \n769: ### 2.4 workload-manager — Sandbox Lifecycle Manager\n770: \n771: **Entry Point**: `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n772: \n773: The workload-manager binary provides REST APIs for sandbox lifecycle management. It creates and manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes.\n774: \n775: #### Command-Line Flags\n776: \n777: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n778: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n779: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n780: | `--store-type` | string | \"redis\" | Store type: redis, valkey |\n781: | `--store-address` | string | \"localhost:6379\" | Store address |\n782: | `--store-password` | string | \"\" | Store password |\n783: | `--store-db` | int | 0 | Store database number |\n784: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default Kubernetes namespace |\n785: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Default session timeout |\n786: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Default max session duration |\n787: | `--gc-interval` | duration | 5m | Garbage collection interval |\n788: | `--gc-worker-count` | int | 5 | GC worker count |\n789: \n790: #### Configuration\n791: \n792: ```go\n793: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n794:     // Server\n795:     ListenAddress string\n796:     \n797:     // Store (Redis/Valkey)\n798:     StoreType    string\n799:     StoreAddress string\n800:     StorePassword string\n801:     StoreDB      int\n802:     \n803:     // Kubernetes\n804:     Namespace string\n805:     \n806:     // Session defaults\n807:     SessionTimeout       time.Duration\n808:     MaxSessionDuration   time.Duration\n809:     \n810:     // Garbage collection\n811:     GCInterval     time.Duration\n812:     GCWorkerCount  int\n813:     \n814:     // Webhook configuration (optional)\n815:     Webhooks []WebhookConfig\n816: }\n817: \n818: type WebhookConfig struct {\n819:     URL        string\n820:     Timeout    int\n821:     RetryCount int\n822: }\n823: ```\n824: \n825: #### API Endpoints\n826: \n827: | Method | Path | Description |\n828: |--------|------|-------------|\n829: | GET | `/health` | Health check |\n830: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Create sandbox |\n831: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | List sandboxes |\n832: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Get sandbox |\n833: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox |\n834: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n835: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n836: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n837: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n838: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n839: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n840: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n841: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n842: \n843: #### Dependencies\n844: \n845: - `pkg/workloadmanager/` — Manager implementation\n846: - `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n847: - `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n848: \n849: ## 3. API Contracts\n850: \n851: ### 3.1 AgentRuntime (CRD)\n852: \n853: **API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n854: **Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n855: **Plural**: `agentruntimes`  \n856: **Short Name**: `ar`\n857: \n858: ```yaml\n859: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n860: kind: AgentRuntime\n861: metadata:\n862:   name: my-agent\n863:   namespace: default\n864: spec:\n865:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n866:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n867:   targetPorts:\n868:     - port: 8080\n869:       protocol: HTTP\n870:       name: http\n871:   podTemplate:\n872:     spec:\n873:       containers:\n874:         - name: agent\n875:           image: my-agent:latest\n876:           resources:\n877:             limits:\n878:               cpu: \"1\"\n879:               memory: \"1Gi\"\n880: status:\n881:   phase: Running\n882:   endpoint: \"http://my-agent.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n883:   conditions:\n884:     - type: Ready\n885:       status: \"True\"\n886:       lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n887: ```\n888: \n889: ### 3.2 CodeInterpreter (CRD)\n890: \n891: **API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n892: **Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n893: **Plural**: `codeinterpreters`  \n894: **Short Name**: `ci`\n895: \n896: ```yaml\n897: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n898: kind: CodeInterpreter\n899: metadata:\n900:   name: my-interpreter\n901:   namespace: default\n902: spec:\n903:   authMode: picod\n904:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n905:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n906:   template:\n907:     image: python:3.11\n908:     command: [\"python\", \"-m\", \"picod\"]\n909:   warmPoolSize: 0\n910: status:\n911:   phase: Running\n912:   endpoint: \"http://my-interpreter.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n913:   ready: true\n914: ```\n915: \n916: ### 3.3 Client-Go Library Usage\n917: \n918: ```go\n919: import (\n920:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n921:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned\"\n922:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n923: )\n924: \n925: config, _ := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"\")\n926: clientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n927: \n928: // Create AgentRuntime\n929: arClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")\n930: agentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n931:     // ... spec\n932: }\n933: result, err := arClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n934: \n935: // List CodeInterpreters\n936: ciClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\")\n937: list, err := ciClient.List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n938: ```\n939: \n940: ## 4. Error Handling\n941: \n942: ### 4.1 Error Codes\n943: \n944: | Code | Name | Description |\n945: |------|------|-------------|\n946: | 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format or parameters |\n947: | 401 | Unauthorized | Authentication failed |\n948: | 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n949: | 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n950: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n951: | 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n952: | 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n953: | 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n954: | 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n955: | 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n956: | 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n957: \n958: ### 4.2 Error Response Format\n959: \n960: ```json\n961: {\n962:   \"error\": {\n963:     \"code\": 404,\n964:     \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n965:     \"details\": {\n966:       \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n967:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n968:       \"namespace\": \"default\"\n969:     }\n970:   }\n971: }\n972: ```\n973: \n974: ### 4.3 Common Errors\n975: \n976: | Error | HTTP Code | Retry | Resolution |\n977: |-------|-----------|-------|------------|\n978: | SandboxNotFound | 404 | No | Check name/namespace |\n979: | DeletionFailed | 500 | Yes | Check K8s cluster state |\n980: | StaleFinalizer | 500 | No | Manual cleanup required |\n981: | OrphanedResource | 500 | Yes | Force delete |\n982: | ResourceNotFound | 404 | No | Resource already deleted |\n983: \n984: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n985: \n986: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n987: \n988: Each binary should have unit tests for:\n989: - Configuration parsing\n990: - Flag handling\n991: - Error cases\n992: \n993: ```go\n994: // Example: router configuration test\n995: func TestRouterConfig(t *testing.T) {\n996:     tests := []struct {\n997:         name    string\n998:         flags   []string\n999:         wantErr bool\n1000:     }{\n1001:         {\n1002:             name:    \"valid config with required flags\",\n1003:             flags:   []string{\"--workload-manager-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\"},\n1004:             wantErr: false,\n1005:         },\n1006:         {\n1007:             name:    \"missing required flag\",\n1008:             flags:   []string{},\n1009:             wantErr: true,\n1010:         },\n1011:     }\n1012:     \n1013:     for _, tt := range tests {\n1014:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n1015:             // Test configuration parsing\n1016:         })\n1017:     }\n1018: }\n1019: ```\n1020: \n1021: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n1022: \n1023: - End-to-end binary startup tests\n1024: - K8s client integration tests (requires test cluster)\n1025: - Store integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n1026: \n1027: ### 5.3 Build Verification\n1028: \n1029: ```bash\n1030: # Build all binaries\n1031: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n1032: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n1033: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n1034: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n1035: \n1036: # Verify binaries exist and are executable\n1037: ls -la bin/\n1038: ```\n1039: \n1040: ## 6. Dependencies\n1041: \n1042: ### 6.1 Go Module Dependencies\n1043: \n1044: ```\n1045: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube          # Main module\n1046:   ├── k8s.io/api                          # K8s API types\n1047:   ├── k8s.io/apimachinery                 # K8s utilities\n1048:   ├── k8s.io/client-go                   # K8s client\n1049:   ├── k8s.io/klog/v2                     # Logging\n1050:   ├── k8s.io/controller-runtime          # Controller framework\n1051:   ├── github.com/gin-gonic/gin            # HTTP framework\n1052:   ├── github.com/redis/go-redis/v9        # Redis client\n1053:   ├── github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go      # Valkey client\n1054:   ├── github.com/prometheus/client_golang # Metrics\n1055:   └── github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5       # JWT support\n1056: ```\n1057: \n1058: ### 6.2 External Dependencies\n1059: \n1060: | Component | Requirement | Description |\n1061: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n1062: | Kubernetes | ≥1.24 | K8s API server |\n1063: | Redis/Valkey | ≥6.0 | Session store |\n1064: | Docker | Optional | For building agent images |\n1065: \n1066: ## 7. Configuration Precedence\n1067: \n1068: Configuration is loaded in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n1069: \n1070: 1. Default values (hardcoded)\n1071: 2. Environment variables (`AGENTCUBE_*`)\n1072: 3. Config file (`/etc/agentcube/config.yaml`)\n1073: 4. Command-line flags\n1074: \n1075: ### 7.1 Environment Variables\n1076: \n1077: | Variable | Binary | Description |\n1078: |----------|--------|-------------|\n1079: | `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` | all | Path to kubeconfig |\n1080: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | all | Default namespace |\n1081: | `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | agentd | Metrics address |\n1082: | `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | router | Backend URL |\n1083: | `ROUTER_STORE_ADDRESS` | router | Redis/Valkey address |\n1084: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_STORE_ADDRESS` | workload-manager | Store address |\n1085: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n1086: \n1087: ### 7.2 Config File Format\n1088: \n1089: ```yaml\n1090: # /etc/agentcube/config.yaml\n1091: apiVersion: v1\n1092: kind: AgentCubeConfig\n1093: metadata:\n1094:   name: agentcube\n1095: spec:\n1096:   namespace: default\n1097:   session:\n1098:     timeout: 15m\n1099:     maxDuration: 8h\n1100:   store:\n1101:     type: redis\n1102:     address: localhost:6379\n1103:     password: \"\"\n1104:   router:\n1105:     listenAddress: \":8080\"\n1106:     workloadManagerURL: \"http://localhost:8081\"\n1107:   workloadManager:\n1108:     listenAddress: \":8081\"\n1109: ```\n1110: \n1111: ## 8. Deployment\n1112: \n1113: ### 8.1 Docker Images\n1114: \n1115: Each binary is packaged as a separate Docker image:\n1116: \n1117: ```dockerfile\n1118: # For agentd, router, workload-manager\n1119: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n1120: WORKDIR /build\n1121: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n1122: RUN go mod download\n1123: COPY . .\n1124: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /agentd ./cmd/agentd\n1125: \n1126: FROM alpine:3.19\n1127: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n1128: COPY --from=builder /agentd /agentd\n1129: ENTRYPOINT [\"/agentd\"]\n1130: ```\n1131: \n1132: ### 8.2 Kubernetes Deployment\n1133: \n1134: The system can be deployed using Helm:\n1135: \n1136: ```yaml\n1137: # values.yaml\n1138: agentd:\n1139:   enabled: true\n1140:   replicas: 1\n1141:   \n1142: router:\n1143:   enabled: true\n1144:   replicas: 2\n1145:   service:\n1146:     type: NodePort\n1147:     port: 80\n1148:     \n1149: workloadManager:\n1150:   enabled: true\n1151:   replicas: 2\n1152:   \n1153: picod:\n1154:   enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n1155: \n1156: ---\n1157: \n1158: # AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod)\n1159: \n1160: - **AR ID**: AR-039\n1161: - **Module**: pkg\n1162: - **Language**: Go\n1163: - **Size**: L\n1164: \n1165: ## 概述\n1166: \n1167: 本任务为 `agentcube` 项目的 router、store 和 picod 三个核心包编写单元测试，覆盖架构设计、数据结构、API 契约、错误处理和测试策略。\n1168: \n1169: ## 架构\n1170: \n1171: ### router 包\n1172: \n1173: **核心组件：**\n1174: \n1175: | 组件 | 文件 | 职责 |\n1176: |------|------|------|\n1177: | `Router` | `server.go` | 主路由器，管理 HTTP 服务器、后端池、认证、中间件 |\n1178: | `BackendPool` | `backend.go` | 后端服务器池，支持路径/Header 路由 |\n1179: | `Backend` | `backend.go` | 单个后端服务器，含健康检查状态 |\n1180: | `RouteHandler` | `route.go` | 路由匹配逻辑 |\n1181: | `Proxy` | `proxy.go` | 请求代理到后端 |\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1181. Use offset=1182 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-021\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a Python-based command-line tool for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. The CLI uses Typer for command parsing and provides a rich user experience with Rich library.\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping\n├── agentcube/","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775883824427,"end":1775883824437}}}}
